title: Independent Abdul Kabir Khan wins PK-27 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate Abdul Kabir Khan has won the Khyber Pakhtunkhwa Assembly election from PK-27 Boner-III by securing 27,821 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was ANP candidate Sardar Hussain who bagged 15,439 votes.
Overall voters turn-out remained 41.63 per cent.
